						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the bund of the tank.</p>						

						<p>Kākatīya: Rudradēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1191, Śukla, Chaitra, śu. 10, Thursday, corresponding to 1269 A.D., March 14.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the gift of land by a certain Aṁnaya to the god Ananta-Gōpīnātha of Dammulapāḍu for the merit of the king.</p>						

